cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and classification of hate speech on Twitter using neural networks. Additionally, the use of pre-trained word embeddings and max/mean pooling are common techniques in NLP research. 

It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with analyzing social media data and detecting hate speech in online communities. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper uses neural networks for classification. 

cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the societal issue of hate speech and its detection on social media platforms. 

Finally, cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely sub-category as it deals with audio processing, but the paper does not mention any audio data.
